==English==
===Etymology===
German, from [[ur-]] + [[Sprache]] ‘speech’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ʊəsprɑ:kə/, ''foreign'' /'u:rʃpra:xə/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|Ursprache|Ursprachen}}
# [[proto-language]]
#:*'''1993''': I had lost him.  He might have been speaking '''Ursprache''', for all that I understood. — Will Self, ''My Idea of Fun''

===Notes===
Ursprache was the winning word at the 2006 [[:Wikipedia:Scripps National Spelling Bee|Scripps National Spelling Bee]]. The winner was [[:Wikipedia:Katharine Close|Katharine Close]].